      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:4:1:11",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ قَبِلَ اللَّهُ مِنْهُ صَلَاةً وَاحِدَةً لَمْ يُعَذِّبْهُ وَ مَنْ قَبِلَ مِنْهُ حَسَنَةً لَمْ يُعَذِّبْهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hafs Bin Al Bakhtary, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one from whom Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Accepts one <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span>, He<sup>azwj</sup> would not Punish him, and the one from whom He<sup>azwj</sup> Accepts a good deeds, He<sup>azwj</sup> would not Punish him’’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "11. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hafs ibn al-Bakhtariy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that whoever 5 s one Salah (prayer) Allah accepts He does not punish him and whoever 5 s one good deed He accepts He does not punish him. 55 "
        ]
      }
